35/*
36 * hb_hashmap_t

38
39extern HB_INTERNAL const hb_codepoint_t minus_1;
40
41template <typename K, typename V,
42 bool minus_one = false>
43struct hb_hashmap_t
44{
45 hb_hashmap_t () { init (); }
46 ~hb_hashmap_t () { fini (); }
47
48 hb_hashmap_t (const hb_hashmap_t& o) : hb_hashmap_t () { resize (new_population: o.population); hb_copy (o, *this); }
49 hb_hashmap_t (hb_hashmap_t&& o) : hb_hashmap_t () { hb_swap (*this, o); }
50 hb_hashmap_t& operator= (const hb_hashmap_t& o) { reset (); resize (new_population: o.population); hb_copy (o, *this); return *this; }
51 hb_hashmap_t& operator= (hb_hashmap_t&& o) { hb_swap (*this, o); return *this; }
52
53 hb_hashmap_t (std::initializer_list<hb_pair_t<K, V>> lst) : hb_hashmap_t ()
54 {
55 for (auto&& item : lst)
56 set (item.first, item.second);
57 }
58 template <typename Iterable,
59 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (Iterable))>
60 hb_hashmap_t (const Iterable &o) : hb_hashmap_t ()
61 {
62 auto iter = hb_iter (o);
63 if (iter.is_random_access_iterator)
64 resize (new_population: hb_len (iter));
65 hb_copy (iter, *this);
66 }
67
68 struct item_t
69 {
70 K key;
71 uint32_t hash : 30;
72 uint32_t is_used_ : 1;
73 uint32_t is_tombstone_ : 1;
74 V value;
75
76 item_t () : key (),
77 hash (0),
78 is_used_ (false), is_tombstone_ (false),
79 value () {}
80
81 bool is_used () const { return is_used_; }
82 void set_used (bool is_used) { is_used_ = is_used; }
83 bool is_tombstone () const { return is_tombstone_; }
84 void set_tombstone (bool is_tombstone) { is_tombstone_ = is_tombstone; }
85 bool is_real () const { return is_used_ && !is_tombstone_; }
86
87 template <bool v = minus_one,
88 hb_enable_if (v == false)>
89 static inline const V& default_value () { return Null(V); };
90 template <bool v = minus_one,
91 hb_enable_if (v == true)>
92 static inline const V& default_value ()
93 {
94 static_assert (hb_is_same (V, hb_codepoint_t), "");
95 return minus_1;
96 };
97
98 bool operator == (const K &o) const { return hb_deref (key) == hb_deref (o); }
99 bool operator == (const item_t &o) const { return *this == o.key; }
100 hb_pair_t<K, V> get_pair() const { return hb_pair_t<K, V> (key, value); }
101 hb_pair_t<const K &, const V &> get_pair_ref() const { return hb_pair_t<const K &, const V &> (key, value); }
102
103 uint32_t total_hash () const
104 { return (hash * 31) + hb_hash (value); }
105 };
106
107 hb_object_header_t header;
108 unsigned int successful : 1; /* Allocations successful */
109 unsigned int population : 31; /* Not including tombstones. */
110 unsigned int occupancy; /* Including tombstones. */
111 unsigned int mask;
112 unsigned int prime;
113 item_t *items;
114
115 friend void swap (hb_hashmap_t& a, hb_hashmap_t& b)
116 {
117 if (unlikely (!a.successful || !b.successful))
118 return;
119 unsigned tmp = a.population;
120 a.population = b.population;
121 b.population = tmp;
122 //hb_swap (a.population, b.population);
123 hb_swap (a.occupancy, b.occupancy);
124 hb_swap (a.mask, b.mask);
125 hb_swap (a.prime, b.prime);
126 hb_swap (a.items, b.items);
127 }
128 void init ()
129 {
130 hb_object_init (this);
131
132 successful = true;
133 population = occupancy = 0;
134 mask = 0;
135 prime = 0;
136 items = nullptr;
137 }
138 void fini ()
139 {
140 hb_object_fini (this);
141
142 if (likely (items)) {
143 unsigned size = mask + 1;
144 for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; i++)
145 items[i].~item_t ();
146 hb_free (items);
147 items = nullptr;
148 }
149 population = occupancy = 0;
150 }
151
152 void reset ()
153 {
154 successful = true;
155 clear ();
156 }
157
158 bool in_error () const { return !successful; }
159
160 bool resize (unsigned new_population = 0)
161 {
162 if (unlikely (!successful)) return false;
163
164 if (new_population != 0 && (new_population + new_population / 2) < mask) return true;
165
166 unsigned int power = hb_bit_storage (v: hb_max ((unsigned) population, new_population) * 2 + 8);
167 unsigned int new_size = 1u << power;
168 item_t *new_items = (item_t *) hb_malloc (size: (size_t) new_size * sizeof (item_t));
169 if (unlikely (!new_items))
170 {
171 successful = false;
172 return false;
173 }
174 for (auto &_ : hb_iter (new_items, new_size))
175 new (&_) item_t ();
176
177 unsigned int old_size = size ();
178 item_t *old_items = items;
179
180 /* Switch to new, empty, array. */
181 population = occupancy = 0;
182 mask = new_size - 1;
183 prime = prime_for (shift: power);
184 items = new_items;
185
186 /* Insert back old items. */
187 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < old_size; i++)
188 {
189 if (old_items[i].is_real ())
190 {
191 set_with_hash (std::move (old_items[i].key),
192 old_items[i].hash,
193 std::move (old_items[i].value));
194 }
195 old_items[i].~item_t ();
196 }
197
198 hb_free (old_items);
199
200 return true;
201 }
202
203 template <typename KK, typename VV>
204 bool set_with_hash (KK&& key, uint32_t hash, VV&& value, bool is_delete=false)
205 {
206 if (unlikely (!successful)) return false;
207 if (unlikely ((occupancy + occupancy / 2) >= mask && !resize ())) return false;
208 item_t &item = item_for_hash (key, hash);
209
210 if (is_delete && !(item == key))
211 return true; /* Trying to delete non-existent key. */
212
213 if (item.is_used ())
214 {
215 occupancy--;
216 if (!item.is_tombstone ())
217 population--;
218 }
219
220 item.key = std::forward<KK> (key);
221 item.value = std::forward<VV> (value);
222 item.hash = hash;
223 item.set_used (true);
224 item.set_tombstone (is_delete);
225
226 occupancy++;
227 if (!is_delete)
228 population++;
229
230 return true;
231 }
232
233 template <typename VV>
234 bool set (const K &key, VV&& value) { return set_with_hash (key, hb_hash (key), std::forward<VV> (value)); }
235 template <typename VV>
236 bool set (K &&key, VV&& value) { return set_with_hash (std::move (key), hb_hash (key), std::forward<VV> (value)); }
237
238 const V& get_with_hash (const K &key, uint32_t hash) const
239 {
240 if (unlikely (!items)) return item_t::default_value ();
241 auto &item = item_for_hash (key, hash);
242 return item.is_real () && item == key ? item.value : item_t::default_value ();
243 }
244 const V& get (const K &key) const
245 {
246 if (unlikely (!items)) return item_t::default_value ();
247 return get_with_hash (key, hash: hb_hash (key));
248 }
249
250 void del (const K &key) { set_with_hash (key, hb_hash (key), item_t::default_value (), true); }
251
252 /* Has interface. */
253 const V& operator [] (K k) const { return get (key: k); }
254 template <typename VV=V>
255 bool has (K key, VV **vp = nullptr) const
256 {
257 if (unlikely (!items))
258 return false;
259 auto &item = item_for_hash (key, hash: hb_hash (key));
260 if (item.is_real () && item == key)
261 {
262 if (vp) *vp = std::addressof (item.value);
263 return true;
264 }
265 else
266 return false;
267 }
268 /* Projection. */
269 V operator () (K k) const { return get (key: k); }
270
271 unsigned size () const { return mask ? mask + 1 : 0; }
272
273 void clear ()
274 {
275 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
276
277 for (auto &_ : hb_iter (items, size ()))
278 {
279 /* Reconstruct items. */
280 _.~item_t ();
281 new (&_) item_t ();
282 }
283
284 population = occupancy = 0;
285 }
286
287 bool is_empty () const { return population == 0; }
288 explicit operator bool () const { return !is_empty (); }
289
290 uint32_t hash () const
291 {
292 return
293 + iter_items ()
294 | hb_reduce ([] (uint32_t h, const item_t &_) { return h ^ _.total_hash (); }, (uint32_t) 0u)
295 ;
296 }
297
298 bool is_equal (const hb_hashmap_t &other) const
299 {
300 if (population != other.population) return false;
301
302 for (auto pair : iter ())
303 if (other.get (pair.first) != pair.second)
304 return false;
305
306 return true;
307 }
308 bool operator == (const hb_hashmap_t &other) const { return is_equal (other); }
309 bool operator != (const hb_hashmap_t &other) const { return !is_equal (other); }
310
311 unsigned int get_population () const { return population; }
312
313 void update (const hb_hashmap_t &other)
314 {
315 if (unlikely (!successful)) return;
316
317 hb_copy (other, *this);
318 }

322 hb_copy (keys() , keys_);

325 void values (hb_set_t &values_) const
326 {
327 hb_copy (values() , values_);

334 auto iter_items () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
335 (
336 + hb_iter (items, size ())
337 | hb_filter (&item_t::is_real)
338 )
339 auto iter_ref () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
340 (
341 + iter_items ()
342 | hb_map (&item_t::get_pair_ref)
343 )
344 auto iter () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
345 (
346 + iter_items ()
347 | hb_map (&item_t::get_pair)
348 )
349 auto keys_ref () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
350 (
351 + iter_items ()
352 | hb_map (&item_t::key)
353 )
354 auto keys () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
355 (
356 + keys_ref ()
357 | hb_map (hb_ridentity)
358 )
359 auto values_ref () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
360 (
361 + iter_items ()
362 | hb_map (&item_t::value)
363 )
364 auto values () const HB_AUTO_RETURN
365 (
366 + values_ref ()
367 | hb_map (hb_ridentity)
368 )
369
370 /* C iterator. */
371 bool next (int *idx,
372 K *key,
373 V *value) const
374 {
375 unsigned i = (unsigned) (*idx + 1);
376
377 unsigned count = size ();
378 while (i < count && !items[i].is_real ())
379 i++;
380
381 if (i >= count)
382 {
383 *idx = -1;
384 return false;
385 }
386
387 *key = items[i].key;
388 *value = items[i].value;
389
390 *idx = (signed) i;
391 return true;
392 }

394 /* Sink interface. */
395 hb_hashmap_t& operator << (const hb_pair_t<K, V>& v)
396 { set (v.first, v.second); return *this; }
397 hb_hashmap_t& operator << (const hb_pair_t<K, V&&>& v)
398 { set (v.first, std::move (v.second)); return *this; }
399 hb_hashmap_t& operator << (const hb_pair_t<K&&, V>& v)
400 { set (std::move (v.first), v.second); return *this; }
401 hb_hashmap_t& operator << (const hb_pair_t<K&&, V&&>& v)
402 { set (std::move (v.first), std::move (v.second)); return *this; }
403
404 item_t& item_for_hash (const K &key, uint32_t hash) const
405 {
406 hash &= 0x3FFFFFFF; // We only store lower 30bit of hash
407 unsigned int i = hash % prime;
408 unsigned int step = 0;
409 unsigned int tombstone = (unsigned) -1;
410 while (items[i].is_used ())
411 {
412 if (items[i].hash == hash && items[i] == key)
413 return items[i];
414 if (tombstone == (unsigned) -1 && items[i].is_tombstone ())
415 tombstone = i;
416 i = (i + ++step) & mask;
417 }
418 return items[tombstone == (unsigned) -1 ? i : tombstone];
419 }
420
421 static unsigned int prime_for (unsigned int shift)
422 {
423 /* Following comment and table copied from glib. */
424 /* Each table size has an associated prime modulo (the first prime
425 * lower than the table size) used to find the initial bucket. Probing
426 * then works modulo 2^n. The prime modulo is necessary to get a
427 * good distribution with poor hash functions.
428 */
429 /* Not declaring static to make all kinds of compilers happy... */
430 /*static*/ const unsigned int prime_mod [32] =
431 {
432 1, /* For 1 << 0 */
433 2,
434 3,
435 7,
436 13,
437 31,
438 61,
439 127,
440 251,
441 509,
442 1021,
443 2039,
444 4093,
445 8191,
446 16381,
447 32749,
448 65521, /* For 1 << 16 */
449 131071,
450 262139,
451 524287,
452 1048573,
453 2097143,
454 4194301,
455 8388593,
456 16777213,
457 33554393,
458 67108859,
459 134217689,
460 268435399,
461 536870909,
462 1073741789,
463 2147483647 /* For 1 << 31 */
464 };
465
466 if (unlikely (shift >= ARRAY_LENGTH (prime_mod)))
467 return prime_mod[ARRAY_LENGTH (prime_mod) - 1];
468
469 return prime_mod[shift];
470 }
471};

474 * hb_map_t

476
477struct hb_map_t : hb_hashmap_t<hb_codepoint_t,
478 hb_codepoint_t,
479 true>
480{
481 using hashmap = hb_hashmap_t<hb_codepoint_t,
482 hb_codepoint_t,
483 true>;
484
485 ~hb_map_t () = default;
486 hb_map_t () : hashmap () {}
487 hb_map_t (const hb_map_t &o) : hashmap ((hashmap &) o) {}
488 hb_map_t (hb_map_t &&o) : hashmap (std::move ((hashmap &) o)) {}
489 hb_map_t& operator= (const hb_map_t&) = default;
490 hb_map_t& operator= (hb_map_t&&) = default;
491 hb_map_t (std::initializer_list<hb_pair_t<hb_codepoint_t, hb_codepoint_t>> lst) : hashmap (lst) {}
492 template <typename Iterable,
493 hb_requires (hb_is_iterable (Iterable))>
494 hb_map_t (const Iterable &o) : hashmap (o) {}
495};
